The `@Column(nullable = false)` annotation adds a not null constraint to the table **definition**, but ***Hibernate or any other framework*** will not perform any **validation** on the entity attribute. Hibernate just executes the SQL INSERT or UPDATE statement, and the database will validate the constraint. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
So, you can use `@Column(nullable = false)` annotation inside the entity.
It can create the SQL insert or update query and pass it to DB without inside-code valiation:

    @Entity
    public class YourClass {
    
        ...
    
        @Column(nullable = false)
        private Date requestLastUpdated;

